HEADWORD: Complexioned
<hw>Com*plex"ioned</hw> <pr>(k⟦ocr⟧m*pl⟦ecr⟧k"sh⟦ucr⟧nd)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <def>Having (such) a complexion; -- used in composition;
<as>as, a dark-<ex>complexioned</ex> or a ruddy-<ex>complexioned</ex>
person</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A flower is the best-<qex>complexioned</qex> grass, as a pearl is
the best-colored clay.</q> <rj><qau>Fuller.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Complexity</ent>⟦br⟧
